caption: Really good gourmet brick oven pizza.
Best pizza on campus, we checked
Bad service, the waiter tried overcharging us. Never checked on our table and dragged to give us our check. Never going again.

Bad experience. I simply ordered one pizza along with a bottle of wine. The waiter never checked on my table for the 40 minutes that I was there but checked on every other table.  After finally checking on our table and removing our plates, he took an additional 10 minutes to hand us the check. He verbally said my order correct but the price looked off to me. I had to click "back" on the device 2-3 times to see the receipt details since he took an additional 5-10 minutes to check if we paid the check only to find out that we were charged two pizzas and a wine bottle. Yes, we were charged $60 out of a $40 order. The waiter went on to say he "mixed tables", mind you only 3 other occupied tables existed, only one which had alcohol, yet they ordered glasses not a bottle and additionally had a different type of alcohol.  - Never checked up on my table. - Definitely prolonged the check. - Verbally stated my order but acted surprised when I showed him what was charged - Made a unreal "mistake" since visually, no other table ordered an identical bottle - Made two comments: When ordered the bottle: "getting drunk!" After finishing the bottle: Acted surprised  Was the waiter trying to purposely overcharge? Wanted a bigger tip? Thought we were drunk enough to just pay and go? That's what I think. I've had many drinks, a half bottle of wine won't be enough to fool me.
Nice authentic pizza in town. Nice wine selections.
Best pizza place in Chambana
Had gluten free menu posted and when I went there said sorry we have discontinued and gave me another set of pizza that I did not need. Pizzas were not bad so I am not trying to bash the outlet.
Pizza was very floppy watery and underwhelming and not worth the price point. The pictures of positive reviews the pizza is substantially thicker so maybe it was a one off but very not worth
Greasy, watery pizza. They don't know how to make a Neopolitan pizza at all. Soggy and bad ingredients.
Price a little high for food.
Great fast true European pizza. Best in Champaign.
This place has great ambiance and staff. On top of that, their food is super authentic! Truly a great experience.
Pizza was not crispy at all and was expensive.
pizza and service here is very good. The service was friendly and sociable. Bring your appetite because portions are large.
Fine scene for delicious Pizza. I give this spot two thumbs up.
Ok location for quality Pizza. visited on sat i believe. i'll return with my friends. ambience is similar to fresno's scene.
Pizza, yeah, my preferred treat. i've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back. prices that won't shock you. menu is similar to a restaurant in el paso i liked.

This place is crazy good! If you enjoy gourmet ingredients, like fresh mozzarella, goat cheese, sweetie drops, house prepare lamb sausage, smoked duck breast, and other phenomenal toppings, Pizzeria Antica is for you! They have traditional toppings like pepperoni or mushroom, but it will be taken to another level by the daily hand made crust and scratch  sauces cooked in genuine artesian ovens...omg! Shout out to Mariano our server extraordinaire. I will try every pizza on the menu!

This is my favorite pizza place in the C-U area. I love the margarita pizza. It tastes very close to the pizzas I got in Italy. Their house red wine is also pretty good. The service is good and the last time I was there they offered indoor and outdoor seating.
Outstanding authentic pizza.

My wife and I have previously shared a date here. The inside was occupied by a fairly spirited bachelorette party so the hostess offered us seating on the back patio. We were fortunate for that accommodation as it was a really cool environment to enjoy a meal together. This isn't your greasy pizza joint, but if you're looking for a change of pace and a cool environment I would highly recommend.
Great pizza

The food was delicious! Their salad and pizza were very unique unlike a few other restaurants I’ve been to. The service was excellent, everything was neat, and I loved the touch of the candles. Very good, I will be back for more! Also, this place has the best gelato ever!
Outstanding pizza 🍕. Made to order in your favorite style. Moderately priced and our waitress gave us awesome service.

Food was pretty solid, but the ambience, food, and price felt incoherent together. Things like paper napkins, table card numbers, and surprisingly not dim lighting made it feel like I should be paying $10-12 for my pizza, not $18.  There was a table to accommodate a large party if you need that (probably 12-14 comfortably). My wife and I came here for a date night the day after Valentine's day, but the vibe is much more "family friendly" than it is "date night." All in all, pretty solid experience, just a fair bit of dissonance between all the different elements.

Great food, but don't expect to be able to order a simple "americanized" pizza here. Atmosphere is quite nice, but the lighting and paper napkins don't quite lend themselves to the romantic atmosphere we had hoped for at the price point of the pizza
Service was great! The food was delicious and not at all like traditional "American" pizza. For the experience it was worth the price.
Great atmosphere. The pizzas are good but small and not worth the price in my opinion.
Limited menu my crust was soggy

This food was amazing. The best pizza that I've ever had. Late Sunday night I ordered a fromage (mushroom pizza). It took a maybe 15 minutes but arrived fresh and hot. Dough was great just chewy enough, ingredients are fresh. Service was amazing. I will be coming back. This is not a casual pizza chain place, but a place you go when toy want some serious Italian style pizza.  11/10
Fantastic pizza, really something different. Should definitely give it a try.
Great pizza
Great pizza, great staff. Cozy and not super costly.
Pistachio pizza was really good.
Truly amazing Italian style pizza. Will come again!

The pizza was good, high quality cheese.  I had the gluten free crust.  It was chewy and crisp on the edges, which is great because GF crusts are tricky.  The toppings were not generous.  It's gourmet type toppings.  The dining room is casual.

I would rate Pizzeria Antica four stars for the food and connection to history and quality ingredients (the ovens are cool!). It doesn't, however, jibe with the open cafe style seating and junk wait service. Our server couldn't keep her hands out of her mouth. We had to prompt her for the check, for boxes, for other things. The other server dropped things not once, but twice, at our table. When we asked for the check (I was going to pay in cash), we got a hefty bill presented to us on an iPad ($70 for a salad, three small but good pizzas, and a can of pop like you'd get at a diner), and that bill gave us the following options for our tip: 18% for basic service, 20% for decent service, 25% for good service, 30% for great service (or something very similar to what I just wrote). I'm sorry, but that type of pretentiousness is enough to keep me from coming back. I've worked in kitchens for over 10 years, and there is a lot about Pizzeria Antica that turned me off. I want to give innovative places good ratings, but come on. Offer good service, make the experience more intimate or fun (to match your price tag), lose the red paper napkins, and let customers choose how they want to tip.
Salad was good. Pizza not so. Plus I believe I was overcharged.
One of the kind variety and very fresh!
Great pizzeria for Italian style pizza. This is uncommon in the Midwest but we love the pizza there. They use great quality ingredients and pizzas are the right size for one person.

Great pizza in downtown Champaign. No draft beers but expansive wine menu. Gelato for desert. Try the salted caramel. Tables in the front and out back for those summer evenings. The tables out back are great for dogs and the service is very attentive.
Antica is one of our favorite spots in Champaign!!
Definite experience, kind of upscale feeling but very authentic Italian. We felt under dressed in jeans and a t shirt. Food was great. Got to try so many new things.
Fantastic and very authentic
Amazing Food! Best pizza ever. Authentic. Delicious salads, Staff helpfull welcoming.  Dessert OUT of THIS WORLD! We'll be back
1 star for each of the minutes it took for me to eat this delicious piece of food. Definitely would recommend.
Their pizza reminds me of Italy! They are dedicated to their craft.
Really great pizza with quality ingredients. Pleasant downtown ambiance. Nice selection of gelato.
Good crust that we used to make our own pizza
Overpriced.
Pizza is good. On the expensive side for the portion you get.
Good pizza. Somewhat pricy. Good service and good staff.
Good pizza. It was bigger than I'd thought, so definitely plan to split one. Very cozy and  nice.
Very unique and authentic pizza. If you want to try the closest thing to authentic, go here. I don't know of any other place in town that comes close
If you are gluten intolerant, do not got there. I ordered a pizza with gluten free crust and for sure it was not!
The Antica Italiano Salad was FANTASTIC and fresh, especially the sweety-drops. The pepperoni pizza was very good as well.
Great, pretty darn close to Italy. Fungi could use more mushrooms but it was very very good. Crust nearly perfect.
Delicious wood fired pizza.  The Margarita pizza is especially good.
The best Italian pizza in town,nice place to enjoy a good wine or Italian beer along with your delicious pizza. Salads are super good too!

Nice place. My wife and I went on a Sunday morning around 11:30 am because our movie was cancelled. We were the only people there but I can see it being packed on Friday or Saturday night.  Good pizza. A little small but if you're not that hungry it will feed two people. Great crust. My wife and I decided that it would be a great place for a first or second date. Nice atmosphere and just enough food so you can chat and get to know someone. We will be going back. Wish there were more appetizer choices.
Excellent pizza!

The atmosphere is great and the pizza is awesome. Would recommend the Funghi or the Anatra for people who like greens on their pizza. The prices are a little high, but for the dough and the way that they cook their pizzas it's definitely worth it.
Great pizza. Average to below average service. Our waitress spent more time studying than waiting on us.
The best pizza.
Really good neopolitan pizza with pretty good service. Restaurant had a great atmosphere and a really good menu selection. I will be back!
Best Italian pizza in Champaign-Urbana. And I'm Italian, by the way. I suggest trying the traditional pizzas.
Place people & food was great Don't be in a hurry and enjoy
Good food,Gelatos amazing! I'd go here all the time!
Very nice environment & food was amazing.
This is the closest you're going to get to real Neopolitan pizza in Champaign. The margherita speciale reminded me of the pizza in Florence. Well worth a visit and the asking price!
Place to go for Italian pizza. If you love Neapolitans food, this is it. Great service too

One of the only places that you can get a Vegan Pizza. I love the pizza dough and the sauce. I would like to have more options of vegan Pizza on the menu, however I am happy to have at least one. The restaurant is very pretty. Vegan Crushed San Marzano Tomato, Fresh Basil, Artichokes, Olives, Mushrooms, Sweety-Drops Please follow me on Instagram @tryatreat
Love the food, so so so good the pizza
Their uniquely spicey and incredibly delicious Diavola pizza, topped with fresh arugula, is the absolute best taste experience, to my palate, in C-U.
The pizza with duck was absolutely heavenly. The gelato is fantastic
Nice. Very tasty pizza, quick service. No alcohol

The pizza was pretty good and the gelato was scrumptious.  The service was lacking.  Not sure what may have been going on but our waitress was not attentive at all and even left our table without taking my husband’s order!  Then when my daughters pizza came out it had no mushrooms and all the waitress said was Mushrooms on pepperoni?  I didn’t hear that!  No offer to remake or anything!  Not even an apology for missing that.  Was a bit disappointing!
This is the best pizza in town
Love it
Authentic pizza; a must try!
Nice place and good fresh pizza. The gelato is also very good

Nice pizza place with wood fired ovens. I had a "Pomodoro" with parmesan cheese, prosciutto, and cherry tomatoes. One pizza serves about one (hungry) person, kids can split a pizza or eat with the parents. The knives are quite dull and make it hard to cut the pizza. Service was good. Checkout is done with some mobile gadget with the server watching you enter the tip (I'm a fine tipper, but like more privacy).
Best neopolitan pizza in area
Beat pizza I’ve ever had
Possibly one of the best places in the country for authentic Neapolitan pizza.

(Translated by Google) Miguel Esteban is very attentive and friendly and makes sure that the pizzas are good.  (Original) Miguel esteban es muy atento y amable y se asegura que las pizzas queden bien buenas.
Best Italian pizza in town! Try the Italian beers too!
The best pizza in Champaign-Urbana

Tired of deep dish and looking for something a little lighter and more sophisticated? Then Pizzeria Antica is a great option in downtown Champaign. Fresh ingredients make for fun pizza options. Service can sometimes be a bit hit or miss, but has never been atrocious. The dining area is open, with high ceilings, so it can sometimes be a bit noisy if they are busy. A good option for large groups as they have a large table in one area, and can move/combine tables elsewhere if necessary.

Neapolitan pizza at its best in Champaign. If you're looking for Stone Street New York level Neapolitan, then trust me this one gets too close!  A must-try should be the cheese one for the freshly San Marzano tomatoes and cheese! Go now
Best Pizza in town.
Yummy yummy Pizza. The place was very generous with their meats cheeses and pizza samples and wine for the Virginia theater goers
Superb wood fire oven pizzas with original recipes and high quality toppings. Highly recommend!
This place is amazing. It is a hospitable environment filled with wonderful workers. Beyond pleased with the great people, and the fantastic pizza.

We have always felt like family here. Ray has always been so engaging and he makes the experience that much more delightful. The handmade wooden toys for the kids, and/or the pizza dough they give the kids to play with is a huge score for parents trying to relax and enjoy a nice time out as a family. Everything on the menu is delicious. The pizza, the salads, the beer and wine, oh the gelato!...and the antipasti! and the oils to dip the bread in! ... I crave it all! It does not disappoint, and if you don't like it, then keep it moving! No need to be downer!
A bit expensive but too simple for me. I guess I am not a fan of pure Italian pizza
Better pizza than all the others. Unique, fast, and good.

Good time, tasty food.  The service was amazing. Cheese plate was a delicious starter. I would prefer a crispier crust on a thin pizza.  My friends and I like to eat family style and the staff was very accommodating. They brought small bowls for salad.  We loved the margarita pizza flavor so much we order a second one.  The gelato was a great dessert! The staff and food made me feel like I was back in Italy!
The pizza here is excellent. I had dinner here with a friend and we had a really nice time. I will definitely be back.

Very slow Sunday at noon. Five tables, but it still took 40 minutes to get our salad. St least the pizza wasn't far behind. They appeared to be under staffed. May be just an off day. Pizza was meh, but could have been a poor choice on our part. Very bland. Wanted to try Pizzeria Antica for a while. Now that I have, I probably wont go back. Disappointing.
Very delicious pizza and a nice staff!!!
If you're looking for real pizza this is the place to go

Great authentic wood-fired pizza.  The margherita pizza is excellent.  Also really enjoyed the pumpkin gelato.  They very kindly brought books for my 2 yr old grandson to look at and were very friendly.  Will be back!
Excellent choice of pizza. We had a table of 7 and the food was delivered quickly. Italian beer was an unexpected addition to the meal. Gelato made for a great dessert.
Salty but good
Very kid friendly! Great pizza
Nice place with great ambience. Great place to hangout with a group
Great place for a first date

The food was delicious but the service was not great. There was only one waitress (I felt bad for her) and so she was always running around. However, she also did not bring our glasses of wine until AFTER we had our salads and our pizza (so basically at the end of the meal).

I ordered the pepperoni pizza it had a fair amount of "juice" on it whether this was from the pepperoni, cheese, or olive oil  I am not sure.  That said the taste was spot on, the pizza was not messy, the bottom of the crust was perfectly crisp, and wait staff was welcoming and seemed happy to be there.
An excellent variety of wood fired pizza, serving until 10 PM. I recommend the Cappicioli, with prosciutto, artichoke, and porcini mushrooms. Pizzas serve one person, give or take.
Very good pizza. Fresh ingredients. A bit loud when there are kids there.
Excellent autentic Italian style pizza. Great service!
Pizzeria Antica has great italian style pizza. Which is good because pizza is basically the whole menu. I personally recommend the vegan pizza (even if you are not vegan) as it is excellent.
Pizza and gelato were excellent.
Great pizza with really Neapolitan taste, my favorite is the funghi with truffle oil and order the infused olive oils as an appetizer!

This is my honest experience. I'd heard people say that this is the most authentic "true" Italian style restaurant in town. Not American-esque pizza, but more traditional style reminiscent of Italia. Walking in, the place was chill, quaint. I looked at the menu and didn't know if I'd like it or not. Don't judge a book by its cover, so I split an individual pizza with my girlfriend, and we can't wait to go back.  P.S.: The gelato is to die for.
One of the best pizza places in Champaign. Italian style thin dough pizza. Prices are okay for students too if you share. I also like their house wine.
Pizza is on point if you like brick oven pizza this is the place for you.  It was our first visit they gave us a free sample of gelato yumm.  We found out pizza place
Best pizza in the Midwest!  But shhhh . . . don't let anyone know.   We want to keep it to ourselves!
Outstanding pizza. Truly Italian!!!
Real Italian pizza tastes
Jusy moved here and looking for fresh made pizza in a wood oven. Service was good and pizza was better. We will be back...
The beer and wine list are impressive, until you find out they are out of many choices. The pizza is quite good, and the Gelato is glorious, but again, they were out of half of their flavors.
Great pizzeria with footbal watchung waiters. Just love the pizza they make.
Excellent pizza. One of the best in town

Extremely overpriced for adequate pizza. Servings were small and bland. Terrible descriptions on the menu. Drinks were extremely small (8oz soda). Service was absolutely horrible and will not be going here again.
Terrible...15 minutes and nobody even came to the table.  No matter how good the food if there is no service then you suck
I didn’t like the food neither the service!
Great meats
Better Italian style pizza than in Italy. Couldn't recommend more

Been here a few times, each visit the pizza was excellent, and the drink pairings are good.  The gelato is good, but maybe not for all American taste buds, as it isn't very sweet (which was good for me).   If you want some wood fired pizza, I recommend the Chimichurri with the lamb sausage, or the Diavola.

The pizza was good, but a little too oily. The building is pretty cool with a laid-back atmosphere. Their selection of wine and beer was nice. Our server suggested a wine based on our conversation and we loved what she suggested. There isn't a lot of parking, so parking at the garage on Hill is easiest.
Great pizza
Close to the Italian style. Hands down best pizza place in town!
If you are in the mood for a different kind of pizza experience... this is the place!
Very authentic italian pizza! I loved it! It was pricey though for no larger than the pizza was.
Loved it. Yummy pizza. I only wanted to taste honey on their 4 cheese pizza.
Great food.  Reminds me of several delicious Neapolitan pizza places in Chicago.  Service was just ok.

The pizza here is a bit more expensive than other pizza places, but it is worth it if you like authentic Italian style. One of our favorites is the pepperoni. Great atmosphere—very open. There are toys for kids in the corner. Always well cleaned. The ice tea is also very good.
Loved eating here. Margherita pizza was delicious and the atmosphere is awesome. Will definitely be going back!
I love this place. Everything is good.

What a nice change of pace from the deep dish scene!  True Italian pizzeria.  Awesome pizza ovens out in the open, great and easy beer and wine list with open airy relaxed dining.  Great to bring kids and if you're sitting near a loud family, it's really not an issue due to the high ceilings.  Do yourself a favor and give it a try.  This is one that shouldn't be missed...
Excellent food an atmosphere! Authentic Italian pizza and good prices. Would definitely recommend!

Relaxed but chic authentic Italian pizza with very fresh ingredients. I love Diavola, and my husband likes the more conventional (but still well done) sassage. We tried the Funghi as well and it was good too.
A bit expensive for a student budget, but amazing. One of the best pizza experiences I've had outside of Italy
Excellent wood fired pie.  Happy to have it in town!
Hands down the best pizza in town.
Good pizza. Good gelato. Great service. That's all I am looking for in life.
This is the most delicious pizza in town
If you like limp dough, this is your place.
Awesome pizza, appetizers salads and gelato!

My husband I recently came back from a trip to Italy and were missing the pizza so we decided to try this place. We weren't disappointed. The pizzas were so fresh and delicious. It was like being back in Italy for a brief amount of time. Can't wait to go back!
Great italian style pizza. I always do take-home. It is quick. The pizza is warm and superb quality.

By far the worst pizza our family has ever had- it was soggy- greasy- terrible service- has potential to be really good but total waste of time- ended up going to another restaurant after receiving our meal after paying for this.
Amazing food and good service. Nice staff :)
Pizza was amazing. Service was awesome. Had the house white wine and the Genziana beer. Both were very good. Split the salami pizza. Was perfect for lunch.

This is a pretty cool restaurant - it has an interesting atmosphere and the pizza is pretty good. I would give it two dollar signs as far as pricing is concerned. The primary reason that I am giving this place 4 stars instead of 5 is because I found the waiting staff to be pushy.
Loved their fancy pizzas. Also loved that I can get gelato there.
Trendy, tasty, handmade, fresh pizza.

Excellent food.  Horrible service. If you are looking for a kind of fancy place with one of the best pizzas in champaign,  this is it. The only problem is that you can not expect a smile and a polite, friendly service. It feels like they do not want you there and they want you to pay and leave as soon as you are done. The staff seemed not to have being trained at all. I have been here 3 times and all times it was the same thing. This is my favorite place for ice cream, expresso coffee and pizza, but the worse place for service in champaign. I always leave frustrated. It's a shame.

Licensed neopolitan pizza, exactly like you'll find in Italy... Same ingredients, made the same way and equally delicious. Good Italian beer as well. If you like neopolitan style pizza, go here when you are in Chambana.
Delicious pizza and nice environment. It is a child friendly place. They have some toys for kidos. I also love the music they play:)!
Pizza was very good, service was good as well.

It was just okay.  We were here for a conference and this place was recommended for having gluten free crust. The server was very uninformed about choices (she didn't know what kinds of Gelato they carry, didn't know about the wines, etc). They did not have the gluten free crust and that order was placed on a small bed of argula and no reduced price.  We asked for individual bills and this didn't happen.
Great pizza and gelato
One of the very few excellent Neapolitan style pizzas I found in the USA.

The pizza here is OK. I don't think it's anything special, but there's not much good pizza in Champaign. I've gotten the margheritta, the diavola, and the goat sausage pizzas. The margheritta always seems a little under done and too doggy from the toppings. Of the three the diavola was the best - everything else I've tried was fairly bland so the spice helps. I do appreciate how easy they make it to split the checks for big groups - when you're done you just go to the front and tell them which part of the ticket you're paying for.
Amazing pizza! My kids couldn't get enough.
High quality pizza with a distinctly Italian kick. Got the classic pepperoni with mushroom. The olive oil platter  antipasto was a very good prelude. And the waitstaff was very friendly!
Really authentic Italian pizza
The food was excellent but the service was terrible.  I will go again for the food and pray the wait staff, including the manager have become more customer oriented.
Best Pizza I've ever had. Funghi is my fave.
Really good pizza!
A little soggyl

What a joy to discover this place. My wife and I recently returned from a month in Italy, and we ate at so many quaint little pizzerias like Antica. I'm a sucker for bufala mozzarella, so I paid the extra money to have it on my margherita pizza. It was delicious. The salads are great, and the gelato is really good. It was like being back in Italy for an hour.
Our 4-year old said, after dinner: "We should come here for dinner every time!"  Great service and ridiculously good pizza, with great atmosphere and friendliness for our family.
Excellent atmosphere and great service. Discussed pizza with chef. Great variety of Italian beers.

Sunday at 6 pm we were the only guests, 2 other tables came later. Waitress had us taste the wine since we couln't decice, I think the wine was too sour (maybe open for too long?) so we did not order any. Pizza was very authentic italian and fresh, quality ingredients for sure. Sadly the crust was burned but the inner part was very very good. If you want authentic italian pizza the place is good, but if you like american style or want it cheaper, go somewhere else. Service was okay although not excellent.

Amazing experience! The pizza is delicious, light, and flavorful. The service was great and our food came quickly. One pizza is enough for two people if you get a side or a second item- two pizzas will give you leftovers. The pizza reheats perfectly in the oven. I'd recommend this restaurant to anyone!
Pizza was super soggy in the middle. Can get much better pizza for a much more reasonable price within a few blocks. Cool atmosphere and good gelato though.

Possibly the worst service experience I have had in Champagin.  The pizza was actually pretty good.  But the service, from start to finish was appalling.   First off, we sat at our table for 20 minutes, with the restaurant 3/4 full at best, waiting for someone to even acknowledge us.    We placed our orders and the food took awhile, but the pizzas were very good.  However, I requested parmesan cheese and it never came.  In fact the server never even checked in with us once to see how we were doing.   After dinner my children wanted some gelato and again, no server ever came to our table to assist.   Finally, at the checkout counter, the host person never even asked us if "everything was OK" or "did you enjoy your meal".    There is potential here,  but the nice decor and decent pizza are going to waste with this inattentive, lacksadasical service.

We stopped in for the first time today. The service was just delightful, the staff being excited to share with us what is special about their offerings (hint, it's all in the ingredients which are top notch, all directly from Italy *or* very local) yet not overwhelming. We ordered a pizza and a large salad to share and loved both. I accidentally ordered us a pizza with meat on it (we're vegetarians) and though it was my error they offered to replace it right away, seeming truly concerned for our experience. We insisted on keeping it as we could easily pick the meat off, but just so thoughtful! The salad was *huge*, splitting it between us we still felt we could have shared it with 1-2 more people as a pre-pizza appetizer. We got gelato too - all from Italy or local Prairie Fruits Farm (goat milk based) - and it was divine. When we mentioned it was our anniversary they brought us two lovely espressos on the house to enjoy our gelato with.  The pizza crust and oils were lovely. Are their things they are still working out? Yes, I think so. When it was clear we were splitting our salad the server offered to bring us another vessel to share it from . . . and brought us the base of a weird to-go container. Little things about the experience were clunky like that, but they were too minimal to remove a star from the review to our minds. If the kindness and delightful attitude of a staff truly proud of where they work is spice to your food (as it is for us) then this is a total 5, on food alone perhaps a 4, but certainly something I can't wait to try again and take family to try out!
The pizza is very authentic Italian style. The service is great and the owners are super friendly. Highly recommend the flavor infused olive oils with your pizza crust.
Overpriced under served. Pizza was ok but made a mistake on order. Toppings a little sparce.
This is definitely the best Italian-style pizza in town.   I have been to Italy multiple times and if you want to experience an authentic taste of Italian-style pizza this is as close as it gets!.
The pizza was superb.
Authentic and delicious! Salads and pizza both were so wonderful can't wait to go back!
Terrific!!!!  The pizza and salads are great and the atmosphere is fun.  Very casual with friendly service.  I will be a regular.
Over priced, under served.  Don't go unless you like to pay more for less.
